            "answer_text": "Roman Concrete. Our modern concrete lasts on average (as I have read, please correct if I\u2019m wrong), 50\u201360 years before problems start to arise, with some exceptions of buildings lasting 150 years without problems. The ancient Romans, however, had concrete that has lasted 2000 years to date and still standing. Unfortunately the recipe was a closely guarded secret and was lost. To the best of my knowledge, we have not yet rediscovered the recipe. ",
